article.headline: Jackson State 65, Texas Southern 60
article.story: JACKSON, Miss. (AP) -- Ishmael Joyce scored 17 points and Jackson State used defense in the second half to defeat Texas Southern 65-60 on Monday night. Jackson State (7-8, 5-1 Southwestern Athletic Conference) held Texas Southern to three baskets in the final six minutes of the game. Jackson State shot just 26 percent in the first half, but outscored Texas Southern 14-2 during a five-minutes stretch of the second half to take a 48-35 lead with 9:44 left in the game. Texas Southern (7-8, 3-2) responded with a 10-1 run to pull to 49-47 on a basket and foul shot from Sean Walker with 6:28 remaining. Walker scored seven points during the spurt. But Texas Southern went cold at the end of the game, missing seven shots in the last six minutes and shooting 4-for-8 from the free-throw line. Jackson State converted six free throws in the final 53 seconds to record its fifth straight home win. K.C. Cavette added 11 points and Antonio Williams-Parker scored 10 for the Tigers. Walker led Texas Southern with 14 points. Lionel Willis and Damien Smith each scored 11.
